t said guild becomes so much tighter, and organised because its not a super easy place to farm if its your first time, your pullers have a lot to learn, your guild in total has a lot to learn...simple things such as do NOT open the door if your fighting (the AoE's will hit the mobs outside and they'll come in and chomp you up), or keeping all melees (except maybe rogues) on same side as the MT on white wyrms so they can't get a CH off. Things like that help promote organisation and team work in your guild.<br><br>so I would say get there as fast as you can, learn, be patient and farm the holy bejesus out of it, and your guilds strength over all will have sky rocketed. Once your done that, Vindi and maybe even statue are yours to beat into oblivion.  Then you can sell all your trak Bp's and what not for some phat peridot funds or better gear for your guild mates and start thinking about west wing and/or NToV.<br><br>I found that HoT was like a starting point to the higher end mobs.<br><br>anyway, hope that helps in some way hehe. peace <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bmonklybusiness43508.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=bergard>Bergard</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Monk-in-Training</span><br>  Posts: 82<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(8/29/02 12:50:00 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=31365.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What equivalent accomplishments is HoT</span><hr size=1> And the most important rule to remember when raiding HoT:<br><br>Ask before opening the door! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><a target="new" href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=30714">Bergard</a> Stormhand<BR>55 Hu