pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=31365.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What equivalent accomplishments is HoT</span><hr size=1> &quot;Our guild is finally to the point we are doing closed raid on Chardok royals.<br><br>We have never gone to the ToV. Would some one rank encounters that would progress me to <br><br>If you can do this &gt; Do this next &gt; Then do this<br><br>to the point that says when you start moving to HoT, or is that where you go first in ToV.&quot;<br><br>Well, I'm assuming you mean king/queen by Royals, not just prince so I'll go based on that.<br><br>Hot dragons are comparable to vox/naggy in difficulty, though a few less hps.<br><br>If your guild isn't well geared and finely tuned, your main concern will be to pull singles as often as possible, especially if your levels aren't high and your dps isn't very good.<br><br>If you can kill Kunark dragons, you can kill the stuff in HoT pretty easily.  None of them use fear, so you won't have any problems there... real trick is to learn the AE's and be prepared with adequate healing and resist gear.<br><br>Bring 18 to 24+ for your first romp with at least 4 clerics until you have a better gauge of the mob's DPS and AE's.  30+ if you're planning on roaming the area on your early trips.  Higher guilds can do HOT with 6 or 12, but don't use that as a guideline until you know what to be ready for.  You'll see what I mean.<br><br>Put your biggest hp/ac tanks on the front line, and don't put resist gear on em.  They'll need ac/hp to tank the mobs.<br><br>Chanters are a must.  Shamans will help reduce healing mana used as well.  Druids can help with resist buffs, and everyone loves having a bard around.<br><br>There are some nameds, and they hit in the 500ish range, so be careful and prepared.  And don't go into Dozekar's room unless you're planning on engaging him (not advisable as he's a significant jump in difficulty).<br><br>You can pull to the door/staging area, though to be honest, crawling rounds of HoT is alot more fun... you'll learn the area, practice positioning and get to the nameds (which are hard to pull from the door... just can't kill fast enough from what you've said of your guild).<br><br>Stuff I'd say keep in mind... careful of wanderers.  One or two wyverns can wreck a smaller guild fast.<br><br>Once you've got HoT under control, you'll be ready to go for some harder stuff.  The tactics will be very different on many of them, but 1300 ac tanks with 5500k+ hps will help alot when you start doing mobs like Vindicator, Velketor, Statue, etc etc etc<br><br>LaotzuQigong<br>60 Grandmaster<br>Legendary<br>The Tribunal <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bmonklybusiness43508.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=dras>Dras</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sucky Monk</span><br>  Posts: 492<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(8/29/02 5:48:34 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=31365.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What equivalent accomplishments is HoT</span><hr size=1> God... will the door rumor never die? <p>-- Dras</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uerrun.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Errun</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Young Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 40<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(8/29/02 6:11:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=31365.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=