lete wipe outs, youll be good to go. It can be done with one or two groups if you have a 60 war and cleric, it also helps to be kinda heavy on melee and healers.<br><br><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=265724>Ryougo</a><br>56 Bubble Master of DRo<br>Evening Reign <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ulaotzuqigong.showPublicProfile?language=EN>LaotzuQigong</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Monk</span><br>  Posts: 241<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(8/29/02 9:32:25 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=31365.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What equivalent accomplishments is HoT</span><hr size=1> HOT mobs and the nameds in HOT are factionless.<br><br>WTOV mobs are -CoV, -Yelinak, +Zek... the nameds are the same in WTOV and have VERY big hits.<br><br>NToV mobs are -Guardians of Veeshan, -CoV, (and no zek hits, so don't expect to get giant faction there).<br><br>LaotzuQigong<br>60 Grandmaster<br>Legendary<br>The Tribunal <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/usiksharn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Siksharn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Young Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 23<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(8/29/02 11:19:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=31365.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What equivalent accomplishments is HoT</span><hr size=1> Why does everyone always say that monks when first pulling HoT are going to have trouble and to expect more then one at a time?<br><br>The first time I went and pulled HoT I came back with singles every time, no wipes to the raid, nothing...<br><br>Heck, even our Paladins can bring back single's when I'm not there.<br><br>What monk in their right mind would bring back more then one mob unless asked to do so in the first place?  HoT is by far the most fun area I have yet to pull.  But make sure if as a monk it is your first time pulling that you have run3 at least.  The mobs will still run faster then you, but run3 helps a lot.<br><br>Enjoy your time with your guild in HoT, after a while like any zone it will become dull and boring but as a  lot of people have stated above, it will increase the power of your guild dramaticly. <p><table><tr><td><table border=0><tr><td style=filter:glow(color=#FF0000 strength=1) align=center>    <font color="#FFFF00" face="Verdana," arial, helvetica, sans-serif size="2"><a target=new href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=97151 ">Siksharn</a><BR>  </font></td></tr><tr><td style=filter:glow(color=#FF0000 strength=1) align=center>    <font color="#FFFF00" face="Verdana," arial, helvetica, sans-serif size="2">55 Master<BR>  </font></td></tr><tr><td style=filter:glow(color=#FF0000 strength=1) align=center>    <font color="#FFFF00" face="Verdana," arial, helvetica, sans-serif size="2">Watchkeepers</font></td></tr></table></td></table></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ujeesan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jeesan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Young Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 17<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(8/30/02 2:51:10 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=31365.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.csl.com/Spod.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What equivalent accomplishments is HoT</span><hr size=1> &quot;Why does everyone always say that monks when first pulling HoT are going to have trouble and to expect more then one at a time?&quot;<br><br>Erm, well nowadays its not so true.. but when I first pulled HOT I died a lot. (I dont think we got past Essendera <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br><br>But remember, some monks pulling HOT for the first time wont have done anything like that before. Go in with 55 range hammers and no AAexp at 55 and you WILL get schooled a few times.<br> <br>/S <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ujeesan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jeesan</A> at: 8/30/02 2:51:35 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/utriliansoulwind.showPublicProfile?language=EN>TrilianSoulwind</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Grand Master</span><br>  Posts: 1142<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(8/30/02 5:22:12 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=31365.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What equivalent accomplishments is HoT</span><hr size=1> Pretty simply, if the entrance to HoT isn't split already, and you've never done it before, its a challenge.<br><br>After that, figuring out which mobs bring extras and which don't is a challenge.<br><br>Thirdly, the melee output of the mobs in HoT are far and beyond anything you'll have faced before.  I'd do a few practice runs in Kael first, personally.  Thats the road I led my guild down, and it worked for us.  We learned all our tactics pulling Dlammaz et al down toward Tormax, and then moved to HoT, the experience proved invaluable.<br><br>Kunark to Velious is a very different game.  You'll simply need to practice. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=1777">Vage Duskbringer</a>  <img src=http://members.home.net/theantar/Vage.jpg><br>Brother of the Lost Circle<br>Disciple of Cazic Thule<br>GRAND Master of the Celestial Fist<br>Guild Leader of Aetherium<br>Quellious server, Level 60</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uazathool.showPublicProfile?language=EN>azathool</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_ball.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master</span><br>  Posts: 834<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(8/30/02 6:07:41 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=31365.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.azathool.com/IMAGES/moving-aza.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What equivalent accomplishments is HoT</span><hr size=1> Bored at work.. so here goes..<br><br>1. Have a plan for getting there.<br><br>It's very important that the &quot;getting there&quot; goes smoothly, as many raids fail before they even start. If half your raid force dies on the way, and several camp out because it's two hours after the &quot;offical&quot; start and people are still getting ports you won't stand a chance in ToV.<br><br>I would suggest BEFORE the whole raid runs there that you have someone check that HoT (=East Wing ToV) is free. A druid who is familiar with the way is best.<br><br>Make sure you set enough time to get there. For those who have never made the trip it can take a good 30 mins.<br><br>Port everyone to CS, Sow, invis &amp; Levi up and run people through to SG. It's best to not use SoE as it gets dispelled in SG because of the lev component. Whereas SOW and lev you will keep the SOW. If you can, leave a cleric/monk in CS to drag the corpses of those who are stupid enough to die to the Sirens at the SG entrance.. Or, alternativly kill the Sirens.<br><br>Succor fragile people across SG if you can. Sure sure, you can run across (I do), but if a soft skinned caster gets stunned by the Sea horsies there they can easily die. As people learn the way, more and more can just run across SG (even our chanters do now). Or again, just kill the three sea horsies that are on the run path.<br><br>The Cleric/monk left in CS can rez those who decided to run for it and got whacked in SG.<br><br>When you zone into WW, SOW people up again if they need it, Invis them (even those COV aligned) and they can run to TOV... If your rich and you have a high enough level Mage you can CoH people there.<br><br>Make sure people know it's the second gorge, and not to jump down the sides of gorges in one go. I've seen so many people fall for 10K damage it's not funny any more.<br><br>CoV aligned people have little to fear in WW... The only dangers are..<br>A. Getting lost.<br>B. Wolves there are KOS to all. Don't try and fight one, they are pretty tough. Just keep away from them, and run fast. Why it's still best to get Invis.<br>C. Escorpa of the Ring.. is on RoS (Ring of Scale) faction.. If your KOS by default, or have killed Kunark dragons then more than likely your KOS.<br>D. Falling down a gorge. 10K damage !<br>E. Being trained with an AoE mob. It's often not safe to sit in WW at the ToV zone in and go AFK, because a lot of KOS people zone in as well, often with AoE'ing mobs hot on their heels (yes, AoE will hit you even if Ally). They can also bring Wolves with them. So just don't go AFK, even if FD.<br><br>If someone is about to die, make sure they get a /loc before expiring. It's a big zone to find a corpse in.<br><br>It's usually a MUST to get at least one cleric to bind outside ToV zone in WW. Don't let them forget !.<br><br>Then zone into ToV and wait in the entrance hall for people to arrive. It's safe, no mobs, and no chance of people getting anywhere near KOS mobs and doing stupid things before the raid starts.<br><br>Get someone to run to HoT to check the way is clear. Reason I say this is that &quot;sometimes&quot; a NToV Wyvern can get stuck. When they get stuck, it's often either in the Hub itself or they can even be dragged into the West Wing. These nasty mobs are KOS to all, and will chomp through 5K hp's in about 5 seconds.<br><br>So the runner is best being a monk. If you do find a &quot;misplaced&quot; mob, hit voiddance and train the sod off somewhere safe.. back into N wing is safest, and then FD. Then get a CoH back. Alternatives to misplaces mobs are clerics bound outside DA'ing the mob off, and then getting a corpse summon and rezing.<br><br>When everyone is in the zone in room, make your groups up and then explain the rules. Then make your way to HoT.<br><br><br>2. Faction. It's usually best that none-KOS to CoV people only do HoT. Dubious or better is fine. I've only ever done HoT with a KOS person once, and it was not easy.<br><br>You can CoH people to HoT from the zone in room, and as long as they never go into LoS of the door they are OK. But it's usually not worth the risk.<br><br>Additionally it makes getting across WW so much easier. The run across WW is a &quot;fun&quot; filled time for me (KOS with all my NTOV killing), and even Invis, SOW'd and Levi'd it can be dangereous. I can attest to the fact that FD works fine whilst flying 100' in the air by GFlux.<br><br>3. ToV layout. Exit the entrance room, and go along the corridor towards the doors at the end. Go past, and your now in the &quot;hub&quot;. This has 4 exits.<br><br>W door is West wing. It's all on CoV faction. If you are CoV aligned, you can go into this area. Right at the end is a zoneout back to WW. In here are named mobs like LtK, Gozz etc. Just be aware that very rarely a NToV wyvern can get stuck here.<br><br>N door is NToV. I'd suggest you do NOT even open the door unless you expect trouble. Very close behind the N door is a room with some very very nasty Wyverns who will eat an ill prepared raid for breakfast, and then sometimes camp their bodies. I know monks are a curious breed, and we think sneak, FD and stonestance can get us anywhere, but until you are prepared, just pretend that door does not exist.<br><br>S door is back to the Entrance hall.<br><br>E door is to the &quot;Testing Halls&quot;. This is what you want.<br><br>Be aware that if you stand in the hub near the E wing door, that AoE will go right though it and hit you. So don't run out and then go AFK just outside it. Safest AFK in ToV is camping.. next is the zone in.<br><br>Also be aware that some guilds when they are doing Iky pull him to the zone in room. Whilst Iky does not have an AoE, they sometimes pull/kill the hall/hub mobs first, and they do have AoE. Also if they wipe to Iky you won't last long as you are KOS by default. <br><br>3. HoT &amp; Etuiquate.<br><br>HoT is KOS to everyone, and normal mobs have no faction hit.<br><br>Beyond the hub door is a room, split both ways in the middle with a pillar and a droppoff.<br><br>Down the dropoff, one on either side are your first mobs, both Wurms. These need splitting first, whilst making sure that there are no wanderers to agro on you, and then kill the three wanderers. Then HoT is yours topull !.<br><br>There are some very simple rules to how to behave in HoT, and this applies to everyone.<br><br>A. Never ever open the door to HoT without asking if it's safe to do so.<br>B. Never open the door during a fight<br>C. Never drag a corpse within LoS (even through a door) without being FD<br>D. Never go within 3 &quot;tiles&quot; (look at the floor, you will see what I mean) of the drop off unless you are puller or tagger.<br>E. Never sit on a pull or during a fight, especially to drakes and wyverns.<br><br>The only person (people) going down the drop off should be the pullers, unless you intend to roam the halls.<br><br>Most &quot;newbie&quot; raids will just sit beyond the hub door, and the puller will grab mobs and pull them to the 1st room where they will either be tagged, or the monk will jump up the ledge and pull them to the guild.<br><br>If you wipe, the cleric just zones back in, and rezes people. Be carefull NOT to drag corpses (see above), and be carefull not to rez within 3 tiles of the edge.<br><br>4. Force needed<br><br>HoT can be done by a single well equipped group of level 60's, but of course that not normally going to be the case.<br><br>The biggest things you need there are..<br><br>A. A good MA. 60th level Warr is best, as most mobs are 60th+, so only a 60th warr can (skill) &quot;taunt&quot; them. However I've seen a 60th SK tank fine, as well as a 59th Warr. You just have to adjust your &quot;all in&quot; slightly.<br><br>B. Slowers. Slowing some of the mobs is almost a must, esp some of the rampaging Wyvern types.<br><br>C. Levels. If at all possible, everyone should be at least 55+. Anyone below 55 will get chewed badly by any AoE. Sure, you can take people lower level, but be prepared to spend large amount of mana healing them, or watch them cower around corners a lot.<br><br>For most guilds starting off there, it's best to wait until you have around 3 group of 55+ people before attempting it.<br><br>Try and get your resists to 100+, and try and have bards singing AoE resist songs if they have them. <br><br><br><br>5. Mobs.<br><br>Mobs come in several types<br><br>A. &quot;Red&quot; wurms. AoE fire based. Rampage at end.<br><br>B. &quot;White&quot; wurms. AoE cold based, CH, gate.<br><br>C. Wyverns. Several varieties, most hit damn hard, some are SK's and HT. Some have nasty damage shields.<br><br>D. Drakes. Several varieties, green (slow), red (fire), blue (gate), black (acid). The green/black ones have nasty dots that are incurable and last ages.<br><br>E. &quot;Butterfly's&quot; (glimmers). Casters, nasty damage shield, gate.<br><br>F. Mini-Named. Most are &quot;drake&quot; models, have a very large number of HP's and hit pretty hard, as well as an AoE.<br><br>G. Dozzekar the Cursed. 1st door opposite the HoT room, down the drop across the way. No real need to go in there, and he will not agro mobs pulled past the corridors either side. Just make sure you keep away from the doors into his room.<br><br>If you get a mob gate, a cleric should immediatly camp. Depending upon where it gates back to can be disastereous. At it's best, some people will be summoned, and run back while the monk tries to re-pull. At it's worste, you will soon be visited by a large number of it's friends.<br><br>Mobs here are prett hard, hit for 400+, have 400 AoE's, and an ill prepared raid party can find themselves facing wipeout very quickly.<br><br>Follow the rules, manage your agro, define your off tanks, get none clerics to patch heal and you will do ok.<br><br>6. Drops.<br><br>Drops are totally random here. You can go two hours with almost nothing, and then suddently get 2 BP's. One day it will appear as though it's all silk, the next plate. This is &quot;normal&quot;. Just put in the hours there (and I'm talking MANY hours.. I think I must have clocked up over a 100 hours in HoT) and you will eventually equip your guild.<br><br>Make a list of who needs what, and make sure it's distributed according to your guild loot rules. Remember, items can be MQ'd, but both parties need Ally CoV to do so.<br><br>Apart from armour, no other loot drops except a few pp, symbols off the mini-named, and tears off Dozz (both for the quests). So if 30 people go on a raid, most will walk away with nothing.<br><br>7. How to pull.<br><br>Well, this bit I'll leave for you to discover for yourself.<br><br>But I'll make a few comments.<br><br>A. After clearing the 2 statics and wanderers, spend a while practising the jump up the ledge. It takes some getting used to.<br>B. Never shrink as a puller (or potential puller). The jump up cannot be done shrunk.<br>C. TIME your kills, esp the 2 entrance statics and wanderers.<br>D. Warping, esp with Wurms is bad here.<br>E. Run 3 helps a lot, and even then Stonestance/MEND is your friend.<br>F. Watch the pathing of mobs. Tag one, and get too far away and it will path off down the HoT corridors.. 30 seconds it will appear with 10 friends. If you do manage to FD, make 100% sure that you drop agro.. Safest is to /q or get a CoH, but if you do get up, stand there for a good minute to test agro.<br><br><br>There are several good maps available for HoT if you look hard enough.<br><br>Hope this helps.<br> <p><br><br><hr><table border="0" width="100%" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">  <tr>    <td width="60">      <p align="center"><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=597"><img border="0" src="http://www.azathool.com/IMAGES/moving-aza.gif" alt="Azathool" width="60" height="60"></a></td>    <td width="100%" bgcolor="#CCCCCC">      <p align="center" style="line-height: 100%; text-indent: 0; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0"><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=597"><b><font face="Monotype Corsiva" size="3" color="#000000">Azathool</font></b></a>      </p>      <p align="center" style="line-height: 100%; text-indent: 0; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0"><a href="http://nightwatchers.dpn.ch"><b><font face="Monotype Corsiva" size="3" color="#000000">NightWatcher</font></b></a></p>      <p align="center" style="line-height: 100%; text-indent: 0; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0"><b><font face="Monotype Corsiva" size="3" color="#000000">7th Hammer</font></b></td>    <td width="60">    <p align="center"><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=4174"><img border="0" src="http://www.azathool.com/IMAGES/moving-wyun.gif" alt="Wyun" width="60" height="60"></a>    </td>  </tr></table><br><br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=le